            Iran's schools and universities offer no sex education
            The Islamic Republic of Iran's national curriculum does not offer any lessons in sex education. According to Iran's Home Office, overall number of divorces is increasing. Analysts suggest that sexual disagreements between couples is a major cause of break-ups. Karen Zarindast reports.Video produced by BBC Persian's Saeedeh Hashemi
                
                        27 Jun 2012
                    
                
        
